message: Prioritize combining two animals from the *same environment* first (e.g., lion + kangaroo, both on land). Immediately use the 'growth serum' on this newly created item to get a high value (often 20-30). Do NOT use the 'growth serum' on an item a second time; it will turn its value negative. The 'mutation catalyst' also seems to consistently result in negative values, so avoid it unless you discover a specific positive interaction. Combine animals from different environments only if you have no same-environment options left; they yield lower initial values (around 5), which the 'growth serum' can then boost (to around 15-25).

Then, use the 'growth serum' tool on each individual ingredient, and especially on this initial hybrid. This consistently yields the highest positive values (up to 30). Also, avoid using the 'growth serum' on an item that is already 'grown' or combining many complex 'grown' items, as these actions also lead to significant negative values. Aim to submit when you have an item around value 30, as higher values are very risky and often drop sharply.

message: Start by combining two items from the same environment (e.g., two water animals). Apply the growth serum to this initial combined item once, maybe twice, but be careful not to 'over-grow' complex hybrids as their value can drop. Separately, use the growth serum repeatedly on a single small ingredient (like a bird, bee, or butterfly) until it reaches 'ultra-grown' status for positive value. The mutation catalyst consistently creates negative values, so avoid it. For your highest score, combine a 'grown' single-environment hybrid with an 'ultra-grown' single ingredient from a *different* environment (e.g., a grown water hybrid with an ultra-grown air animal). Avoid combining too many components or highly complex items, as this often leads to a sharp decrease in value.
